    "# Notebook 2/5 — ASR-SSL v1 — FIXED v3\n",
    "## Mean-Teacher + ATP + ATC + ADR on MS-CBAM-Transformer\n",
    "\n",
    "**Root cause identified in v2:** `warmup_train_step` still used `[-20:]` variable slice (wrong layers).  \n",
    "ATC collapsing due to T=0.5 over-sharpening. LR too high for a pre-trained backbone.\n",
    "\n",
    "### v3 Fixes:\n",
    "| # | Fix |\n",
    "|---|-----|\n",
    "| F1 | Warmup uses explicitly named `_warmup_vars` list (not a slice) |\n",
    "| F2 | Sharpen T=0.5→**T=0.8** (softer — prevents ATC collapse) |\n",
    "| F3 | SSL LR_MAX=3e-4→**1e-4** (pre-trained backbone needs gentle LR) |\n",
    "| F4 | cons loss too large: clamp W_CONS_MAX=1.0→**0.5**, ramp 20 epochs |\n",
    "| F5 | Warmup epochs 5→**10** to fully recover N1 val baseline before SSL |\n",
    "| F6 | EMA decay during warmup disabled (teacher only updated in SSL phase) |\n"
   ]
